[I] A fast compiler cache

[T] Ccache is a compiler cache. It speeds up re-compilation of C/C++ code by
[T] caching previous compiles and detecting when the same compile is being
[T] done again.

[U] https://ccache.samba.org/

[A] Andrew Tridgell
[M] Rene Rebe <rene@t2-project.org>

[C] base/development
[F] CROSS DIETLIBC NO-LTO.gcc

[E] opt fmt
[E] opt xxhash
[E] opt zstd

[L] GPL
[S] Stable
[V] 4.13
[P] X 0-2--5---9 105.400

[CV-URL] https://ccache.dev/download.html
[D] f391ce54d59e56e4d788fb2a2ef92292244e0e75beff22650c4e899f ccache-4.13.tar.xz https://github.com/ccache/ccache/releases/download/v4.13/

var_append cmakeopt ' ' '-DUSE_CCACHE=OFF -DENABLE_TESTING=OFF -DREDIS_STORAGE_BACKEND=OFF'
